{
  "stem": "1033.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And it's difficult for me, if not impossible-- and I would say the latter-- to assume that there is any kind of preordained higher power that would have helped Hitler to achieve all this.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I think I very much see in everything that I have ever looked at, the machinations of man, not God, in any aspect of the world, past, present, or future.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And at the same time, I must tell you that I do now and I have always believed in God.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But it isn't a kind of God of hocus pocus, of books that-- everybody's got their own books to thump, and their own interpretation, which are, it seems to me, usually self-serving.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And I do not wish to offend with this observation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And I do have respect for whatever people believe in, provided it does not hurt anyone else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's Birkenau, really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Auschwitz was a city, an industrial center.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Usually when people talk about Auschwitz, they mean Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the death camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, to go back to the visual for a moment, there were camps on each side of us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you were facing the trains as they were coming in, which was the center of this compound, to the left were a woman's camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We could see bald ladies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We couldn't talk to them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The wires were electrified, and about a yard from the electric wire, there was a single wire running.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And every now and again, there were guard towers where a guard was watching, presumably with guns.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have never noticed anybody being shot from there, but they were there, or at least the towers were there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I couldn't see whether somebody was inside or not.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On the other side were the twin camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were called [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
